Revenue in 2Q grew 11%yoy (MSe: +10%), operating profit grew 9% (MSe: 11%). Fx gains continue to help net profit grow to 15%yoy (MSe: +11%).
In 2Q, to- C business revenue grew 9.3% (domestic \(+ > 15\%\) , overseas +LSD), and to- B revenue grew 16.6%.
The company is confident to achieve double digit revenue growth for 2025 (vs prior guidance of HSD to low teens), with higher net profit growth.
It is confident to achieve positive sales and profit growth each quarter in 2H25 despite a higher base, which is better than expectation.
There could be some uncertainty in 2026 given the high base. But it expects a long- term sales growth at MSD to HSD%.

- By region, in 1H25, ToC segment for North America, South America, Europe, Asia, Middle East and Africa grew more than double digit, double digit, \(>25\%\) \(>20\%\) , high single digit and \(>20\%\) (1Q: 38%, 38%, 43%, 34%, 20% and 33% yoy), respectively, with order front loading due to tariff changes.- Overseas sales: Order growth pressured in 2Q, but started to turn positive yoy growth in July/August. In emerging markets, OBM business is better than OEM. OBM margin is-0.8ppt lower than OEM as it is still in the investment cycle, with room for margin expansion.- AC: Installation cards grew \(>15\%\) yoy in July. The company is confident of achieving double digit revenue growth for full year. The company is focused on market share and is flexible to adjust prices, according to market competition.  
- Margin: OPM compressed 0.2ppt yoy in 2Q (narrower than 0.6ppt compression in 1Q), with lower GPM (-1ppt) offset by selling expenses savings (0.7ppt) and FX gains.
Interim DPS of Rmb0.5 (15% payout ratio of 1H25 net profit).
